ACTIVE.tooltip: Objects in world that are running a script or currently physically moving.

AGENT.tooltip: Objects in world that are agents.

AGENT_AUTOMATED.tooltip: The agent has been identified as a scripted agent

AGENT_FLOATING_VIA_SCRIPTED_ATTACHMENT.tooltip: The agent is floating via scripted attachment.

AGENT_LIST_PARCEL.tooltip: Agents on the same parcel where the script is running.

AGENT_LIST_PARCEL_OWNER.tooltip: Agents on any parcel in the region where the parcel owner is the same as the owner of the parcel under the scripted object.

ATTACH_AVATAR_CENTER.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's geometric centre.

ATTACH_FACE_LEAR.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left ear (extended).

ATTACH_FACE_LEYE.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left eye (extended).

ATTACH_FACE_REAR.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right ear (extended).

ATTACH_FACE_REYE.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right eye (extended).

ATTACH_HIND_LFOOT.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left hind foot.

ATTACH_HIND_RFOOT.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right hind foot.

ATTACH_LEAR.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left ear.

ATTACH_LEFT_PEC.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left pectoral.

ATTACH_LEYE.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left eye.

ATTACH_LFOOT.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left foot.

ATTACH_LHAND.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left hand.

ATTACH_LHAND_RING1.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left ring finger.

ATTACH_LHIP.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left hip.

ATTACH_LLARM.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left lower arm.

ATTACH_LLLEG.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's lower left leg.

ATTACH_LPEC.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right pectoral. (Deprecated, use ATTACH_RIGHT_PEC)

ATTACH_LSHOULDER.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left shoulder.

ATTACH_LUARM.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left upper arm.

ATTACH_LULEG.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's lower upper leg.

ATTACH_LWING.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left wing.

ATTACH_REAR.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right ear.

ATTACH_REYE.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right eye.

ATTACH_RFOOT.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right foot.

ATTACH_RHAND.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right hand.

ATTACH_RHAND_RING1.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right ring finger.

ATTACH_RHIP.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right hip.

ATTACH_RIGHT_PEC.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right pectoral.

ATTACH_RLARM.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right lower arm.

ATTACH_RLLEG.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right lower leg.

ATTACH_RPEC.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's left pectoral. (deprecated, use ATTACH_LEFT_PEC)

ATTACH_RSHOULDER.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right shoulder.

ATTACH_RUARM.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right upper arm.

ATTACH_RULEG.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right upper leg.

ATTACH_RWING.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's right wing.

ATTACH_TAIL_BASE.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's tail base.

ATTACH_TAIL_TIP.tooltip: Attach to the avatar's tail tip.

BEACON_MAP.tooltip: Cause llMapBeacon to optionally display and focus the world map on the avatar's viewer.

CHANGED_ALLOWED_DROP.tooltip: The object inventory has changed because an item was added through the llAllowInventoryDrop interface.

CHANGED_LINK.tooltip: The object has linked or its links were broken.

CHANGED_SHAPE.tooltip: The object base shape has changed, e.g., a box to a cylinder.

CHANGED_TEXTURE.tooltip: The texture offset, scale rotation, or simply the object texture has changed.

CHARACTER_ACCOUNT_FOR_SKIPPED_FRAMES.tooltip: If set to false, character will not attempt to catch up on lost time when pathfinding performance is low, potentially providing more reliable movement (albeit while potentially appearing to be more stuttery). Default is true to match pre-existing behavior.

CHARACTER_AVOIDANCE_MODE.tooltip: Allows you to specify that a character should not try to avoid other characters, should not try to avoid dynamic obstacles (relatively fast moving objects and avatars), or both.

CHARACTER_CMD_JUMP.tooltip: Makes the character jump. Requires an additional parameter, the height to jump, between 0.1m and 2.0m. This must be provided as the first element of the llExecCharacterCmd option list.

CHARACTER_DESIRED_SPEED.tooltip: Speed of pursuit in meters per second.

CHARACTER_DESIRED_TURN_SPEED.tooltip: The character's maximum speed while turning about the Z axis. - Note that this is only loosely enforced.

CHARACTER_LENGTH.tooltip: Set collision capsule length - cannot be less than two times the radius.

CHARACTER_MAX_TURN_RADIUS.tooltip: The character's turn radius when travelling at CHARACTER_MAX_TURN_SPEED.

CHARACTER_STAY_WITHIN_PARCEL.tooltip: Determines whether a character can leave its starting parcel.\nTakes a boolean parameter. If TRUE, the character cannot voluntarilly leave the parcel, but can return to it.

CHARACTER_TYPE.tooltip: Specifies which walk-ability coefficient will be used by this character.

CLICK_ACTION_BUY.tooltip: When the prim is clicked, the buy dialog is opened.

CLICK_ACTION_DISABLED.tooltip: No click action. No touches detected or passed.

CLICK_ACTION_IGNORE.tooltip: No click action. Object is invisible to the mouse.

CLICK_ACTION_NONE.tooltip: Performs the default action: when the prim is clicked, touch events are triggered.

CLICK_ACTION_OPEN.tooltip: When the prim is clicked, the object inventory dialog is opened.

CLICK_ACTION_OPEN_MEDIA.tooltip: When the prim is touched, the web media dialog is opened.

CLICK_ACTION_PAY.tooltip: When the prim is clicked, the pay dialog is opened.

CLICK_ACTION_PLAY.tooltip: When the prim is clicked, html-on-a-prim is enabled?

CLICK_ACTION_SIT.tooltip: When the prim is clicked, the avatar sits upon it.

CLICK_ACTION_TOUCH.tooltip: When the prim is clicked, touch events are triggered.

CLICK_ACTION_ZOOM.tooltip: Zoom in on object when clicked.

COMBAT_CHANNEL.tooltip: COMBAT_CHANNEL is an integer constant that, when passed to llRegionSay will add the message to the combat log. A script with a chat listen active on COMBAT_CHANNEL may also monitor the combat log.

CONTENT_TYPE_HTML.tooltip: "text/html", only valid for embedded browsers on content owned by the person viewing. Falls back to "text/plain" otherwise.

CONTROL_BACK.tooltip: Test for the avatar move back control.

CONTROL_DOWN.tooltip: Test for the avatar move down control.

CONTROL_FWD.tooltip: Test for the avatar move forward control.

CONTROL_LBUTTON.tooltip: Test for the avatar left button control.

CONTROL_LEFT.tooltip: Test for the avatar move left control.

CONTROL_ML_LBUTTON.tooltip: Test for the avatar left button control while in mouse look.

CONTROL_RIGHT.tooltip: Test for the avatar move right control.

CONTROL_ROT_LEFT.tooltip: Test for the avatar rotate left control.

CONTROL_ROT_RIGHT.tooltip: Test for the avatar rotate right control.

CONTROL_UP.tooltip: Test for the avatar move up control.

DAMAGEABLE.tooltip: Objects in world that are able to process damage.

DAMAGE_TYPE_ACID.tooltip: Damage caused by a caustic substance, such as acid

DAMAGE_TYPE_BLUDGEONING.tooltip: Damage caused by a blunt object, such as a club.

DAMAGE_TYPE_COLD.tooltip: Damage inflicted by exposure to extreme cold

DAMAGE_TYPE_FIRE.tooltip: Damage inflicted by exposure to heat or flames.

DAMAGE_TYPE_FORCE.tooltip: Damage inflicted by a great force or impact.

DAMAGE_TYPE_IMPACT.tooltip: System damage generated by imapact with land or a prim.

DAMAGE_TYPE_NECROTIC.tooltip: Damage caused by a direct assault on life-force

DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING.tooltip: Damage caused by a piercing object such as a bullet, spear, or arrow.

DAMAGE_TYPE_PSYCHIC.tooltip: Damage caused by a direct assault on the mind.

DAMAGE_TYPE_RADIANT.tooltip: Damage caused by radiation or extreme light.

DAMAGE_TYPE_SLASHING.tooltip: Damage caused by a slashing object such as a sword or axe.

DAMAGE_TYPE_SONIC.tooltip: Damage caused by loud noises, like a Crash Worship concert.

DATA_BORN.tooltip: The date the agent was born, returned in ISO 8601 format of YYYY-MM-DD.

DATA_ONLINE.tooltip: TRUE for online, FALSE for offline.

DATA_RATING.tooltip:
Returns the agent ratings as a comma separated string of six integers. They are:
			1) Positive rated behaviour
			2) Negative rated behaviour
			3) Positive rated appearance
			4) Negative rated appearance
			5) Positive rated building
			6) Negative rated building

DEBUG_CHANNEL.tooltip: DEBUG_CHANNEL is an integer constant that, when passed to llSay, llWhisper, or llShout as a channel parameter, will print text to the Script Warning/Error Window.

DEG_TO_RAD.tooltip:
0.017453293 - Number of radians per degree.
			You can use this to convert degrees to radians by multiplying the degrees by this number.

DENSITY.tooltip: Used with llSetPhysicsMaterial to enable the density value. Must be between 1.0 and 22587.0 (in Kg/m^3 -- see if you can figure out what 22587 represents)

DEREZ_DIE.tooltip: Causes the object to immediately die.

DEREZ_MAKE_TEMP.tooltip: The object is made temporary and will be cleaned up at some later timer.

DEREZ_TO_INVENTORY.tooltip: The object is returned to the inventory of the rezzer.

ENV_INVALID_AGENT.tooltip: Could not find agent with the specified ID

ENV_INVALID_RULE.tooltip: Attempted to change an unknown property.

ENV_NOT_EXPERIENCE.tooltip: Attempt to change environments outside an experience.

ENV_NO_ENVIRONMENT.tooltip: Could not find environmental settings in object inventory.

ENV_NO_EXPERIENCE_LAND.tooltip: The experience has not been enabled on this land.

ENV_NO_EXPERIENCE_PERMISSION.tooltip: Agent has not granted permission to change environments.

ENV_NO_PERMISSIONS.tooltip: Script does not have permission to modify environment.

ENV_THROTTLE.tooltip: Could not validate values for environment.

ENV_VALIDATION_FAIL.tooltip: Could not validate values for environment.

EOF.tooltip: Indicates the last line of a notecard was read.

ESTATE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_AGENT_ADD.tooltip: Add the agent to this estate's Allowed Residents list.

ESTATE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_AGENT_REMOVE.tooltip: Remove the agent from this estate's Allowed Residents list.

ESTATE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_GROUP_ADD.tooltip: Add the group to this estate's Allowed groups list.

ESTATE_ACCESS_ALLOWED_GROUP_REMOVE.tooltip: Remove the group from this estate's Allowed groups list.

ESTATE_ACCESS_BANNED_AGENT_ADD.tooltip: Add the agent to this estate's Banned residents list.

ESTATE_ACCESS_BANNED_AGENT_REMOVE.tooltip: Remove the agent from this estate's Banned residents list.

FALSE.tooltip: An integer constant for boolean comparisons. Has the value '0'.

FORCE_DIRECT_PATH.tooltip: Makes character navigate in a straight line toward position. May be set to TRUE or FALSE.

FRICTION.tooltip: Used with llSetPhysicsMaterial to enable the friction value. Must be between 0.0 and 255.0

GRAVITY_MULTIPLIER.tooltip: Used with llSetPhysicsMaterial to enable the gravity multiplier value. Must be between -1.0 and +28.0

HTTP_ACCEPT.tooltip:
Provide a string value to be included in the HTTP
            accepts header value. This replaces the default Second Life HTTP accepts header.

HTTP_CUSTOM_HEADER.tooltip: Add an extra custom HTTP header to the request. The first string is the name of the parameter to change, e.g. "Pragma", and the second string is the value, e.g. "no-cache". Up to 8 custom headers may be configured per request. Note that certain headers, such as the default headers, are blocked for security reasons.

HTTP_EXTENDED_ERROR.tooltip: Report extended error information through http_response event.

HTTP_PRAGMA_NO_CACHE.tooltip: Allows enabling/disbling of the "Pragma: no-cache" header.\nUsage: [HTTP_PRAGMA_NO_CACHE, integer SendHeader]. When SendHeader is TRUE, the "Pragma: no-cache" header is sent by the script. This matches the default behavior. When SendHeader is FALSE, no "Pragma" header is sent by the script.

HTTP_USER_AGENT.tooltip:
Provide a string value to be included in the HTTP
            User-Agent header value. This is appended to the default value.

LAND_LARGE_BRUSH.tooltip: Use a large brush size.\nNOTE: This value is incorrect, a large brush should be 2.

LAND_MEDIUM_BRUSH.tooltip: Use a medium brush size.\nNOTE: This value is incorrect, a medium brush should be 1.

LAND_SMALL_BRUSH.tooltip: Use a small brush size.\nNOTE: This value is incorrect, a small brush should be 0.

LINKSETDATA_DELETE.tooltip: A name:value pair has been removed from the linkset datastore.

LINKSETDATA_EMEMORY.tooltip: A name:value pair was too large to write to the linkset datastore.

LINKSETDATA_EPROTECTED.tooltip: The name:value pair has been protected from overwrite in the linkset datastore.

LINKSETDATA_MULTIDELETE.tooltip: A CSV list of names removed from the linkset datastore.

LINKSETDATA_NOTFOUND.tooltip: The named key was not found in the datastore.

LINKSETDATA_NOUPDATE.tooltip: The value written to a name in the keystore is the same as the value already there.

LINKSETDATA_OK.tooltip: The name:value pair was written to the datastore.

LINKSETDATA_RESET.tooltip: The linkset datastore has been reset.

LINKSETDATA_UPDATE.tooltip: A name:value pair in the linkset datastore has been changed or created.

LINK_ALL_CHILDREN.tooltip: This targets every object except the root in the linked set.

LINK_ALL_OTHERS.tooltip: This targets every object in the linked set except the object with the script.

LINK_ROOT.tooltip: This targets the root of the linked set.

LINK_SET.tooltip: This targets every object in the linked set.

LINK_THIS.tooltip: The link number of the prim containing the script.

MASK_COMBINED.tooltip: Fold permissions for object inventory into results.

NAK.tooltip: Indicates a notecard read was attempted and the notecard was not yet cached on the server.

OBJECT_ACCOUNT_LEVEL.tooltip:
Retrieves the account level of an avatar.
Returns 0 when the avatar has a basic account,
 1 when the avatar has a premium account,
 10 when the avatar has a premium plus account,
 or -1 if the object is not an avatar.

OBJECT_ANIMATED_COUNT.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the number of associated animated objects

OBJECT_ANIMATED_SLOTS_AVAILABLE.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the number of additional animated object attachments allowed.

OBJECT_ATTACHED_POINT.tooltip: Gets the attachment point to which the object is attached.\nReturns 0 if the object is not an attachment (or is an avatar, etc).

OBJECT_ATTACHED_SLOTS_AVAILABLE.tooltip: Returns the number of attachment slots available.\nReturns 0 if the object is not an avatar or none are available.

OBJECT_BODY_SHAPE_TYPE.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the body type of the avatar, based on shape data.\nIf no data is available, -1.0 is returned.\nThis is normally between 0 and 1.0, with 0.5 and larger considered 'male'

OBJECT_CLICK_ACTION.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the click action.\nThe default is 0

OBJECT_CREATION_TIME.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the time this object was created

OBJECT_CREATOR.tooltip: Gets the object's creator key. If id is an avatar, a NULL_KEY is returned.

OBJECT_DAMAGE.tooltip: Gets the damage value assigned to this object.

OBJECT_DAMAGE_TYPE.tooltip: Gets the damage type, if any, assigned to this object.

OBJECT_DESC.tooltip: Gets the object's description. If id is an avatar, an empty string is returned.

OBJECT_GROUP.tooltip: Gets the prims's group key. If id is an avatar, a NULL_KEY is returned.

OBJECT_GROUP_TAG.tooltip: Gets the agent's current group role tag. If id is an object, an empty is returned.

OBJECT_HEALTH.tooltip: Gets current health value for the object.

OBJECT_HOVER_HEIGHT.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get hover height of the avatar\nIf no data is available, 0.0 is returned.

OBJECT_LAST_OWNER_ID.tooltip: Gets the object's last owner ID.

OBJECT_LINK_NUMBER.tooltip: Gets the object's link number or 0 if unlinked.

OBJECT_OWNER.tooltip: Gets an object's owner's key. If id is group owned, a NULL_KEY is returned.

OBJECT_PATHFINDING_TYPE.tooltip: Returns the pathfinding setting of any object in the region. It returns an integer matching one of the OPT_* constants.

OBJECT_PERMS_COMBINED.tooltip: Gets the object's permissions including any inventory.

OBJECT_PHANTOM.tooltip: Returns boolean, detailing if phantom is enabled or disabled on the object.\nIf id is an avatar or attachment, 0 is returned.

OBJECT_PHYSICS.tooltip: Returns boolean, detailing if physics is enabled or disabled on the object.\nIf id is an avatar or attachment, 0 is returned.

OBJECT_POS.tooltip: Gets the object's position in region coordinates.

OBJECT_PRIM_COUNT.tooltip: Gets the prim count of the object.  The script and target object  must be owned by the same owner

OBJECT_RENDER_WEIGHT.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the Avatar_Rendering_Cost of an avatar, based on values reported by nearby viewers.\nIf no data is available, -1 is returned.\nThe maximum render weight stored by the simulator is 500000. When called against an object, 0 is returned.

OBJECT_REZ_TIME.tooltip: Get the time when an object was rezzed.

OBJECT_ROOT.tooltip: Gets the id of the root prim of the object requested.\nIf id is an avatar, return the id of the root prim of the linkset the avatar is sitting on (or the avatar's own id if the avatar is not sitting on an object within the region).

OBJECT_SELECT_COUNT.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the number of avatars selecting any part of the object

OBJECT_SIT_COUNT.tooltip: This is a flag used with llGetObjectDetails to get the number of avatars sitting on the object

OBJECT_TEMP_ATTACHED.tooltip: Returns boolean, indicating if object is a temp attachment.

OBJECT_TEMP_ON_REZ.tooltip: Returns boolean, detailing if temporary is enabled or disabled on the object.

OBJECT_TEXT_ALPHA.tooltip: Gets the alpha of an objects hover text.

OBJECT_TEXT_COLOR.tooltip: Gets the color of an objects hover text.

OBJECT_TOTAL_INVENTORY_COUNT.tooltip: Gets the total inventory count of the object.  The script and target object must be owned by the same owner

OPT_LEGACY_LINKSET.tooltip: Returned for movable obstacles, movable phantoms, physical, and volumedetect objects.

OPT_OTHER.tooltip: Returned for attachments, Linden trees, and grass.

PARCEL_DETAILS_AREA.tooltip: The parcel's area, in square meters. (5 chars.).

PARCEL_DETAILS_DESC.tooltip: The description of the parcel. (127 chars).

PARCEL_DETAILS_LANDING_LOOKAT.tooltip: Lookat vector set for teleport routing.

PARCEL_DETAILS_LANDING_POINT.tooltip: The parcel's landing point, if any.

PARCEL_DETAILS_NAME.tooltip: The name of the parcel. (63 chars.).

PARCEL_DETAILS_PRIM_USED.tooltip: The number of prims used on this parcel.

PARCEL_DETAILS_SCRIPT_DANGER.tooltip: There are restrictions on this parcel that may impact script execution.

PARCEL_DETAILS_SEE_AVATARS.tooltip: The parcel's avatar visibility setting. (1 char.).

PARCEL_MEDIA_COMMAND_DESC.tooltip: Use this to get or set the parcel media description.

PARCEL_MEDIA_COMMAND_LOOP_SET.tooltip: Used to get or set the parcel's media looping variable.

PARCEL_MEDIA_COMMAND_SIZE.tooltip: Use this to get or set the parcel media pixel resolution.

PARCEL_MEDIA_COMMAND_TYPE.tooltip: Use this to get or set the parcel media MIME type (e.g. "text/html").

PASS_IF_NOT_HANDLED.tooltip: Pass the event if there is no script handling the event in the prim.

PERMISSION_ATTACH.tooltip: If this permission is enabled, the object can successfully call llAttachToAvatar to attach to the given avatar.

PERMISSION_CHANGE_LINKS.tooltip: If this permission is enabled, the object can successfully call llCreateLink, llBreakLink, and llBreakAllLinks to change links to other objects.

PERMISSION_DEBIT.tooltip: If this permission is enabled, the object can successfully call llGiveMoney or llTransferLindenDollars to debit the owners account.

PERMISSION_SILENT_ESTATE_MANAGEMENT.tooltip: A script with this permission does not notify the object owner when it modifies estate access rules via llManageEstateAccess.

PERMISSION_TAKE_CONTROLS.tooltip: If this permission enabled, the object can successfully call the llTakeControls libray call.

PERMISSION_TRIGGER_ANIMATION.tooltip: If this permission is enabled, the object can successfully call llStartAnimation for the avatar that owns this.

PI.tooltip: 3.14159265 - The number of radians in a semi-circle.

PING_PONG.tooltip: Play animation going forwards, then backwards.

PI_BY_TWO.tooltip: 1.57079633 - The number of radians in a quarter circle.

PRIM_ALLOW_UNSIT.tooltip: Prim parameter for restricting manual standing for seated avatars in an experience.\nIgnored if the avatar was not seated via a call to llSitOnLink.

PRIM_ALPHA_MODE.tooltip:
Prim parameter for materials using integer face, integer alpha_mode, integer alpha_cutoff.
Defines how the alpha channel of the diffuse texture should be rendered.
Valid options for alpha_mode are PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_BLEND, _NONE, _MASK, and _EMISSIVE.
alpha_cutoff is used only for PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_MASK.

PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_BLEND.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_ALPHA_MODE.\nIndicates that the diffuse texture's alpha channel should be rendered as alpha-blended.

PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_EMISSIVE.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_ALPHA_MODE.\nIndicates that the diffuse texture's alpha channel should be rendered as an emissivity mask.

PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_MASK.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_ALPHA_MODE.\nIndicates that the diffuse texture's alpha channel should be rendered as fully opaque for alpha values above alpha_cutoff and fully transparent otherwise.

PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_NONE.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_ALPHA_MODE.\nIndicates that the diffuse texture's alpha channel should be ignored.

PRIM_COLLISION_SOUND.tooltip: Collision sound uuid and volume for this prim

PRIM_COLOR.tooltip:
[PRIM_COLOR, integer face, vector color, float alpha]
integer face  face number or ALL_SIDES vector color  color in RGB <R, G, B> (<0.0, 0.0, 0.0> = black, <1.0, 1.0, 1.0> = white) float alpha  from 0.0 (clear) to 1.0 (solid) (0.0 <= alpha <= 1.0)

PRIM_DAMAGE.tooltip: Damage and damage type assigned to this prim.

PRIM_FLEXIBLE.tooltip: [ PRIM_FLEXIBLE, integer boolean, integer softness, float gravity, float friction, float wind, float tension, vector force ] + +integer boolean  TRUE enables, FALSE disables +integer softness  ranges from 0 to 3 +float gravity  ranges from -10.0 to 10.0 +float friction  ranges from 0.0 to 10.0 +float wind  ranges from 0.0 to 10.0 +float tension  ranges from 0.0 to 10.0 +vector force

PRIM_GLOW.tooltip: PRIM_GLOW is used to get or set the glow status of the face.\n[ PRIM_GLOW, integer face, float intensity ]

PRIM_GLTF_ALPHA_MODE_BLEND.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_GLTF_BASE_COLOR alpha mode "BLEND".

PRIM_GLTF_ALPHA_MODE_MASK.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_GLTF_BASE_COLOR alpha mode "MASK".

PRIM_GLTF_ALPHA_MODE_OPAQUE.tooltip: Prim parameter setting for PRIM_GLTF_BASE_COLOR alpha mode "OPAQUE".

PRIM_GLTF_BASE_COLOR.tooltip: Prim parameter for materials using integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians, vector color, integer alpha_mode, float alpha_cutoff, boolean double_sided.\nValid options for alpha_mode are PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_BLEND, _NONE, and _MASK.\nalpha_cutoff is used only for PRIM_ALPHA_MODE_MASK.

PRIM_GLTF_EMISSIVE.tooltip: Prim parameter for GLTF materials using integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians, vector color

PRIM_GLTF_METALLIC_ROUGHNESS.tooltip: Prim parameter for GLTF materials using integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians, float metallic_factor, float roughness_factor

PRIM_GLTF_NORMAL.tooltip: Prim parameter for GLTF materials using integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians

PRIM_LINK_TARGET.tooltip:
[ PRIM_LINK_TARGET, integer link_target ]
Used to get or set multiple links with a single PrimParameters call.

PRIM_MEDIA_ALT_IMAGE_ENABLE.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets the default image state (the image that the user sees before a piece of media is active) for the chosen face. The default image is specified by Second Life's server for that media type.

PRIM_MEDIA_AUTO_LOOP.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets whether auto-looping is enabled.

PRIM_MEDIA_AUTO_PLAY.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets whether the media auto-plays when a Resident can view it.

PRIM_MEDIA_AUTO_SCALE.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets whether auto-scaling is enabled. Auto-scaling forces the media to the full size of the texture.

PRIM_MEDIA_AUTO_ZOOM.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets whether clicking the media triggers auto-zoom and auto-focus on the media.

PRIM_MEDIA_CONTROLS.tooltip: Integer. Gets/Sets the style of controls. Can be either PRIM_MEDIA_CONTROLS_STANDARD or PRIM_MEDIA_CONTROLS_MINI.

PRIM_MEDIA_CONTROLS_MINI.tooltip: Mini web navigation controls; does not include an address bar.

PRIM_MEDIA_CURRENT_URL.tooltip: String. Gets/Sets the current url displayed on the chosen face. Changing this URL causes navigation. 1024 characters Maximum.

PRIM_MEDIA_FIRST_CLICK_INTERACT.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets whether the first click interaction is enabled.

PRIM_MEDIA_HEIGHT_PIXELS.tooltip: Integer. Gets/Sets the height of the media in pixels.

PRIM_MEDIA_HOME_URL.tooltip: String. Gets/Sets the home URL for the chosen face. 1024 characters maximum.

PRIM_MEDIA_PERMS_CONTROL.tooltip: Integer. Gets/Sets the permissions mask that control who can see the media control bar above the object:: PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_ANYONE, PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_GROUP, PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_NONE, PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_OWNER

PRIM_MEDIA_PERMS_INTERACT.tooltip: Integer. Gets/Sets the permissions mask that control who can interact with the object: PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_ANYONE, PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_GROUP, PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_NONE, PRIM_MEDIA_PERM_OWNER

PRIM_MEDIA_WHITELIST.tooltip: String. Gets/Sets the white-list as a string of escaped, comma-separated URLs. This string can hold up to 64 URLs or 1024 characters, whichever comes first.

PRIM_MEDIA_WHITELIST_ENABLE.tooltip: Boolean. Gets/Sets whether navigation is restricted to URLs in PRIM_MEDIA_WHITELIST.

PRIM_MEDIA_WIDTH_PIXELS.tooltip: Integer. Gets/Sets the width of the media in pixels.

PRIM_NORMAL.tooltip: Prim parameter for materials using integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians

PRIM_OMEGA.tooltip:
[ PRIM_OMEGA, vector axis, float spinrate, float gain ]
vector axis  arbitrary axis to rotate the object around float spinrate  rate of rotation in radians per second float gain  also modulates the final spinrate and disables the rotation behavior if zero

PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_CONVEX.tooltip: Use the convex hull of the prim shape for physics (this is the default for mesh objects).

PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_NONE.tooltip: Ignore this prim in the physics shape. NB: This cannot be applied to the root prim.

PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_PRIM.tooltip: Use the normal prim shape for physics (this is the default for all non-mesh objects).

PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_TYPE.tooltip:
Allows you to set the physics shape type of a prim via lsl. Permitted values are:
			PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_NONE, PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_PRIM, PRIM_PHYSICS_SHAPE_CONVEX

PRIM_POINT_LIGHT.tooltip:
[ PRIM_POINT_LIGHT, integer boolean, vector linear_color, float intensity, float radius, float falloff ]
integer boolean  TRUE enables, FALSE disables vector linear_color  linear color in RGB <R, G, B&> (<0.0, 0.0, 0.0> = black, <1.0, 1.0, 1.0> = white) float intensity  ranges from 0.0 to 1.0 float radius  ranges from 0.1 to 20.0 float falloff  ranges from 0.01 to 2.0

PRIM_POSITION.tooltip:
[ PRIM_POSITION, vector position ]
vector position  position in region or local coordinates depending upon the situation

PRIM_POS_LOCAL.tooltip:
PRIM_POS_LOCAL, vector position ]
vector position - position in local coordinates

PRIM_PROJECTOR.tooltip: [ PRIM_PROJECTOR, string texture, float fov, float focus, float ambiance ]

PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE.tooltip: Allows you to configure the object as a custom-placed reflection probe, for image-based lighting (IBL). Only objects in the influence volume of the reflection probe object are affected.

PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE_BOX.tooltip: This is a flag option used with llGetPrimitiveParams and related functions when the parameter is PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE. When set, the reflection probe is a box. When unset, the reflection probe is a sphere.

PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE_DYNAMIC.tooltip: This is a flag option used with llGetPrimitiveParams and related functions when the parameter is PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE. When set, the reflection probe includes avatars in IBL effects. When unset, the reflection probe excludes avatars.

PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE_MIRROR.tooltip: This is a flag option used with llGetPrimitiveParams and related functions when the parameter is PRIM_REFLECTION_PROBE. When set, the reflection probe acts as a mirror.

PRIM_SCRIPTED_SIT_ONLY.tooltip: Prim parameter for restricting manual sitting on this prim.\nSitting must be initiated via call to llSitOnLink.

PRIM_SCULPT_FLAG_MIRROR.tooltip: Render an X axis mirror of the sculpty.

PRIM_SIT_TARGET.tooltip: [ PRIM_SIT_TARGET, integer boolean, vector offset, rotation rot ]

PRIM_SPECULAR.tooltip: Prim parameter for materials using integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians, vector color, integer glossy, integer environment

PRIM_TEXT.tooltip: [ PRIM_TEXT, string text, vector color, float alpha ]

PRIM_TEXTURE.tooltip: [ PRIM_TEXTURE, integer face, string texture, vector repeats, vector offsets, float rotation_in_radians ]

PSYS_PART_BOUNCE_MASK.tooltip: Particles bounce off of a plane at the objects Z height.

PSYS_PART_END_ALPHA.tooltip: A float which determines the ending alpha of the object.

PSYS_PART_END_COLOR.tooltip: A vector <r, g, b> which determines the ending color of the object.

PSYS_PART_END_SCALE.tooltip: A vector <sx, sy, z>, which is the ending size of the particle billboard in meters (z is ignored).

PSYS_PART_FLAGS.tooltip: Each particle that is emitted by the particle system is simulated based on the following flags. To use multiple flags, bitwise or (|) them together.

PSYS_PART_FOLLOW_SRC_MASK.tooltip: The particle position is relative to the source objects position.

PSYS_PART_FOLLOW_VELOCITY_MASK.tooltip: The particle orientation is rotated so the vertical axis faces towards the particle velocity.

PSYS_PART_INTERP_COLOR_MASK.tooltip: Interpolate both the color and alpha from the start value to the end value.

PSYS_PART_INTERP_SCALE_MASK.tooltip: Interpolate the particle scale from the start value to the end value.

PSYS_PART_MAX_AGE.tooltip: Age in seconds of a particle at which it dies.

PSYS_PART_START_ALPHA.tooltip: A float which determines the starting alpha of the object.

PSYS_PART_START_COLOR.tooltip: A vector <r.r, g.g, b.b> which determines the starting color of the object.

PSYS_PART_START_SCALE.tooltip: A vector <sx, sy, z>, which is the starting size of the particle billboard in meters (z is ignored).

PSYS_PART_TARGET_POS_MASK.tooltip: The particle heads towards the location of the target object as defined by PSYS_SRC_TARGET_KEY.

PSYS_PART_WIND_MASK.tooltip: Particles have their velocity damped towards the wind velocity.

PSYS_SRC_ACCEL.tooltip: A vector <x, y, z> which is the acceleration to apply on particles.

PSYS_SRC_ANGLE_BEGIN.tooltip: Area in radians specifying where particles will NOT be created (for ANGLE patterns)

PSYS_SRC_ANGLE_END.tooltip: Area in radians filled with particles (for ANGLE patterns) (if lower than PSYS_SRC_ANGLE_BEGIN, acts as PSYS_SRC_ANGLE_BEGIN itself, and PSYS_SRC_ANGLE_BEGIN acts as PSYS_SRC_ANGLE_END).

PSYS_SRC_BURST_PART_COUNT.tooltip: How many particles to release in a burst.

PSYS_SRC_BURST_RADIUS.tooltip: What distance from the center of the object to create the particles.

PSYS_SRC_BURST_RATE.tooltip: How often to release a particle burst (float seconds).

PSYS_SRC_BURST_SPEED_MAX.tooltip: Maximum speed that a particle should be moving.

PSYS_SRC_BURST_SPEED_MIN.tooltip: Minimum speed that a particle should be moving.

PSYS_SRC_INNERANGLE.tooltip:
Specifies the inner angle of the arc created by the PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE or PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE_CONE source pattern.
			The area specified will NOT have particles in it.

PSYS_SRC_MAX_AGE.tooltip: How long this particle system should last, 0.0 means forever.

PSYS_SRC_OMEGA.tooltip: Sets the angular velocity to rotate the axis that SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE and SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE_CONE use.

PSYS_SRC_OUTERANGLE.tooltip:
Specifies the outer angle of the arc created by the PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE or PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE_CONE source pattern.
			The area between the outer and inner angle will be filled with particles.

PSYS_SRC_PATTERN.tooltip:
The pattern which is used to generate particles.
			Use one of the following values: PSYS_SRC_PATTERN Values.

PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE.tooltip: Shoot particles across a 2 dimensional area defined by the arc created from PSYS_SRC_OUTERANGLE. There will be an open area defined by PSYS_SRC_INNERANGLE within the larger arc.

PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_ANGLE_CONE.tooltip: Shoot particles out in a 3 dimensional cone with an outer arc of PSYS_SRC_OUTERANGLE and an inner open area defined by PSYS_SRC_INNERANGLE.

PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_DROP.tooltip: Drop particles at the source position.

PSYS_SRC_PATTERN_EXPLODE.tooltip: Shoot particles out in all directions, using the burst parameters.

PSYS_SRC_TARGET_KEY.tooltip: The key of a target object to move towards if PSYS_PART_TARGET_POS_MASK is enabled.

PSYS_SRC_TEXTURE.tooltip: An asset name for the texture to use for the particles.

PUBLIC_CHANNEL.tooltip: PUBLIC_CHANNEL is an integer constant that, when passed to llSay, llWhisper, or llShout as a channel parameter, will print text to the publicly heard chat channel.

PURSUIT_FUZZ_FACTOR.tooltip: Selects a random destination near the offset.

PURSUIT_INTERCEPT.tooltip: Define whether the character attempts to predict the target's location.

PURSUIT_OFFSET.tooltip: Go to a position offset from the target.

PU_EVADE_HIDDEN.tooltip: Triggered when an llEvade character thinks it has hidden from its pursuer.

PU_EVADE_SPOTTED.tooltip: Triggered when an llEvade character switches from hiding to running

PU_FAILURE_INVALID_GOAL.tooltip: Goal is not on the navigation-mesh and cannot be reached.

PU_FAILURE_INVALID_START.tooltip: Character cannot navigate from the current location - e.g., the character is off the navmesh or too high above it.

PU_FAILURE_NO_NAVMESH.tooltip: This is a fatal error reported to a character when there is no navmesh for the region. This usually indicates a server failure and users should file a bug report and include the time and region in which they received this message.

PU_FAILURE_NO_VALID_DESTINATION.tooltip: There is no good place for the character to go - e.g., it is patrolling and all the patrol points are now unreachable.

PU_FAILURE_TARGET_GONE.tooltip: Target (for llPursue or llEvade) can no longer be tracked - e.g., it left the region or is an avatar that is now more than about 30m outside the region.

PU_FAILURE_UNREACHABLE.tooltip: Goal is no longer reachable for some reason - e.g., an obstacle blocks the path.

PU_GOAL_REACHED.tooltip: Character has reached the goal and will stop or choose a new goal (if wandering).

RAD_TO_DEG.tooltip: 57.2957795 - Number of degrees per radian. You can use this number to convert radians to degrees by multiplying the radians by this number.

REQUIRE_LINE_OF_SIGHT.tooltip: Define whether the character needs a line-of-sight to give chase.

RESTITUTION.tooltip: Used with llSetPhysicsMaterial to enable the density value. Must be between 0.0 and 1.0

REZ_ACCEL.tooltip: Acceleration forced applied to the rezzed object. [vector force, integer rel]

REZ_DAMAGE.tooltip: Damage applied by the object when it collides with an agent. [float damage]

REZ_DAMAGE_TYPE.tooltip: Set the damage type applied when this object collides.

REZ_FLAGS.tooltip: Rez flags to set on the newly rezzed object. [integer flags]

REZ_FLAG_DIE_ON_COLLIDE.tooltip: Object will die after its first collision.

REZ_FLAG_DIE_ON_NOENTRY.tooltip: Object will die if it attempts to enter a parcel that it can not.

REZ_FLAG_NO_COLLIDE_FAMILY.tooltip: Object will not trigger collision events with other objects created by the same rezzer.

REZ_FLAG_NO_COLLIDE_OWNER.tooltip: Object will not trigger collision events with its owner.

REZ_FLAG_PHANTOM.tooltip: Make the object phantom on rez.

REZ_FLAG_PHYSICAL.tooltip: Make the object physical on rez.

REZ_FLAG_TEMP.tooltip: Flag the object as temp on rez.

REZ_LOCK_AXES.tooltip: Prevent the object from rotating around some axes. [vector locks]

REZ_OMEGA.tooltip: Omega applied to the rezzed object. [vector axis, integer rel, float spin, float gain]

REZ_PARAM.tooltip: Integer value to pass to the object as its rez parameter. [integer param]

REZ_PARAM_STRING.tooltip: A string value to pass to the object as its rez parameter. [string param]

REZ_POS.tooltip: Position at which to rez the new object. [vector position, integer rel, integer atroot]

REZ_ROT.tooltip: Rotation applied to newly rezzed object. [rotation rot, integer rel]

REZ_SOUND.tooltip: Sound attached to the rezzed object. [string name, float volume, integer loop]

REZ_SOUND_COLLIDE.tooltip: Sound played by the object on a collision. [string name, float volume]

REZ_VEL.tooltip: Initial velocity of rezzed object. [vector vel, integer rel, integer inherit]

SIM_STAT_AGENT_MS.tooltip: Time spent in 'agent' segment of simulation frame.

SIM_STAT_CHILD_AGENT_COUNT.tooltip: Number of child agents in region.

SIM_STAT_IMAGE_MS.tooltip: Time spent in 'image' segment of simulation frame.

SIM_STAT_NET_MS.tooltip: Time spent in 'network' segment of simulation frame.

SIM_STAT_OTHER_MS.tooltip: Time spent in 'other' segment of simulation frame.

SIM_STAT_PCT_CHARS_STEPPED.tooltip: Returns the % of pathfinding characters skipped each frame, averaged over the last minute.\nThe returned value corresponds to the "Characters Updated" stat in the viewer's Statistics Bar.

SIM_STAT_PHYSICS_MS.tooltip: Time spent in 'physics' segment of simulation frame.

SIM_STAT_SCRIPT_MS.tooltip: Time spent in 'script' segment of simulation frame.

SIM_STAT_SCRIPT_RUN_PCT.tooltip: Percent of scripts run during frame.

SIT_FLAG_ALLOW_UNSIT.tooltip: The prim allows a seated avatar to stand up.

SIT_FLAG_NO_COLLIDE.tooltip: The seated avatar's hit box is disabled when seated on this prim.

SIT_FLAG_NO_DAMAGE.tooltip: Damage will not be forwarded to an avatar seated on this prim.

SIT_FLAG_SCRIPTED_ONLY.tooltip: An avatar may not manually sit on this prim.

SIT_FLAG_SIT_TARGET.tooltip: The prim has an explicitly set sit target.

SIT_INVALID_AGENT.tooltip: Avatar ID did not specify a valid avatar.

SIT_INVALID_LINK.tooltip: Link ID did not specify a valid prim in the linkset or resolved to multiple prims.

SIT_INVALID_OBJECT.tooltip: Attempt to force an avatar to sit on an attachment or other invalid target.

SIT_NOT_EXPERIENCE.tooltip: Attempt to force an avatar to sit outside an experience.

SIT_NO_ACCESS.tooltip: Avatar does not have access to the parcel containing the target linkset of the forced sit.

SIT_NO_EXPERIENCE_PERMISSION.tooltip: Avatar has not granted permission to force sits.

SIT_NO_SIT_TARGET.tooltip: No available sit target in linkset for forced sit.

SKY_AMBIENT.tooltip: The ambient color of the environment

SKY_CLOUDS.tooltip: Settings controlling cloud density and configuration

SKY_DENSITY_PROFILE_COUNTS.tooltip: Counts for density profiles of each type.

SKY_GAMMA.tooltip: The gamma value applied to the scene.

SKY_GLOW.tooltip: Glow color applied to the sun and moon.

SKY_PLANET.tooltip: Planet information used in rendering the sky.

SKY_REFLECTION_PROBE_AMBIANCE.tooltip: Settings the ambience of the reflection probe.

SKY_REFRACTION.tooltip: Sky refraction parameters for rainbows and optical effects.

SKY_TEXTURE_DEFAULTS.tooltip: Is the environment using the default textures.

SMOOTH.tooltip: Slide in the X direction, instead of playing separate frames.

SOUND_SYNC.tooltip: Sound will be synchronized with the nearest master.

SOUND_TRIGGER.tooltip: Sound will be triggered at the prim's location and not attached.

STATUS_BLOCK_GRAB.tooltip: Controls whether the object can be grabbed.\nA grab is the default action when in third person, and is available as the hand tool in build mode. This is useful for physical objects that you don't want other people to be able to trivially disturb. The default is FALSE

STATUS_BLOCK_GRAB_OBJECT.tooltip: Prevent click-and-drag movement on all prims in the object.

STATUS_BOUNDS_ERROR.tooltip: Argument(s) passed to function had a bounds error.

STATUS_DIE_AT_EDGE.tooltip: Controls whether the object is returned to the owners inventory if it wanders off the edge of the world.\nIt is useful to set this status TRUE for things like bullets or rockets. The default is TRUE

STATUS_DIE_AT_NO_ENTRY.tooltip: Controls whether the object dies if it attempts to enter a parcel that does not allow object entry or does not have enough capacity.\nIt is useful to set this status TRUE for things like bullets or rockets. The default is FALSE

STATUS_MALFORMED_PARAMS.tooltip: Function was called with malformed parameters.

STATUS_NOT_FOUND.tooltip: Object or other item was not found.

STATUS_OK.tooltip: Result of function call was a success.

STATUS_PHANTOM.tooltip: Controls/indicates whether the object collides or not.\nSetting the value to TRUE makes the object non-colliding with all objects. It is a good idea to use this for most objects that move or rotate, but are non-physical. It is also useful for simulating volumetric lighting. The default is FALSE.

STATUS_PHYSICS.tooltip: Controls/indicates whether the object moves physically.\nThis controls the same flag that the UI check-box for Physical controls. The default is FALSE.

STATUS_ROTATE_Z.tooltip:
Controls/indicates whether the object can physically rotate around
			the specific axis or not. This flag has no meaning
			for non-physical objects. Set the value to FALSE
			if you want to disable rotation around that axis. The
			default is TRUE for a physical object.
			A useful example to think about when visualizing
			the effect is a sit-and-spin device. They spin around the
			Z axis (up) but not around the X or Y axis.

STATUS_SANDBOX.tooltip:
Controls/indicates whether the object can cross region boundaries
			and move more than 20 meters from its creation
			point. The default if FALSE.

STATUS_TYPE_MISMATCH.tooltip: Argument(s) passed to function had a type mismatch.

TARGETED_EMAIL_OBJECT_OWNER.tooltip: Send email to the owner of the object

TARGETED_EMAIL_ROOT_CREATOR.tooltip: Send email to the creator of the root object

TP_ROUTING_BLOCKED.tooltip: Direct teleporting is blocked on this parcel.

TP_ROUTING_FREE.tooltip: Teleports are unrestricted on this parcel.

TP_ROUTING_LANDINGP.tooltip: Teleports are routed to a landing point if set on this parcel.

TRANSFER_BAD_ROOT.tooltip: The root path specified in TRANSFER_DEST contained an invalid directory or was reduced to nothing.

TRANSFER_DEST.tooltip: The root folder to transfer inventory into.

TRANSFER_FLAGS.tooltip: Flags to control the behavior of inventory transfer.

TRANSFER_FLAG_COPY.tooltip: Gives a copy of the object being transfered. Implies TRANSFER_FLAG_TAKE.

TRANSFER_FLAG_TAKE.tooltip: On a successful transfer, automatically takes the object into inventory.

TRANSFER_NO_ATTACHMENT.tooltip: Can not transfer ownership of an attached object.

TRANSFER_NO_ITEMS.tooltip: No items in the inventory list are eligible for transfer.

TRANSFER_NO_PERMS.tooltip: The object does not have transfer permissions.

TRANSFER_NO_TARGET.tooltip: Could not find the receiver in the current region.

TRANSFER_OK.tooltip: Inventory transfer offer was successfully made.

TRAVERSAL_TYPE.tooltip: One of TRAVERSAL_TYPE_FAST, TRAVERSAL_TYPE_SLOW, and TRAVERSAL_TYPE_NONE.

TRUE.tooltip: An integer constant for boolean comparisons. Has the value '1'.

TYPE_FLOAT.tooltip: The list entry is a float.

TYPE_INTEGER.tooltip: The list entry is an integer.

TYPE_KEY.tooltip: The list entry is a key.

TYPE_ROTATION.tooltip: The list entry is a rotation.

TYPE_STRING.tooltip: The list entry is a string.

TYPE_VECTOR.tooltip: The list entry is a vector.

VEHICLE_ANGULAR_DEFLECTION_EFFICIENCY.tooltip: A slider between minimum (0.0) and maximum (1.0) deflection of angular orientation. That is, its a simple scalar for modulating the strength of angular deflection such that the vehicles preferred axis of motion points toward its real velocity.

VEHICLE_ANGULAR_DEFLECTION_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The time-scale for exponential success of linear deflection deflection. Its another way to specify the strength of the vehicles tendency to reorient itself so that its preferred axis of motion agrees with its true velocity.

VEHICLE_ANGULAR_FRICTION_TIMESCALE.tooltip:
A vector of timescales for exponential decay of the vehicles angular velocity about its preferred axes of motion (at, left, up).
			Range = [0.07, inf) seconds for each element of the vector.

VEHICLE_ANGULAR_MOTOR_DECAY_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The timescale for exponential decay of the angular motors magnitude.

VEHICLE_ANGULAR_MOTOR_DIRECTION.tooltip: The direction and magnitude (in preferred frame) of the vehicles angular motor.The vehicle will accelerate (or decelerate if necessary) to match its velocity to its motor.

VEHICLE_ANGULAR_MOTOR_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The timescale for exponential approach to full angular motor velocity.

VEHICLE_BANKING_EFFICIENCY.tooltip: A slider between anti (-1.0), none (0.0), and maxmum (1.0) banking strength.

VEHICLE_BANKING_MIX.tooltip: A slider between static (0.0) and dynamic (1.0) banking. "Static" means the banking scales only with the angle of roll, whereas "dynamic" is a term that also scales with the vehicles linear speed.

VEHICLE_BANKING_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The timescale for banking to exponentially approach its maximum effect. This is another way to scale the strength of the banking effect, however it affects the term that is proportional to the difference between what the banking behavior is trying to do, and what the vehicle is actually doing.

VEHICLE_BUOYANCY.tooltip: A slider between minimum (0.0) and maximum anti-gravity (1.0).

VEHICLE_FLAG_BLOCK_INTERFERENCE.tooltip: Prevent other scripts from pushing vehicle.

VEHICLE_FLAG_HOVER_UP_ONLY.tooltip: Hover does not push down. Use this flag for hovering vehicles that should be able to jump above their hover height.

VEHICLE_FLAG_LIMIT_MOTOR_UP.tooltip: Prevents ground vehicles from motoring into the sky.

VEHICLE_FLAG_LIMIT_ROLL_ONLY.tooltip: For vehicles with vertical attractor that want to be able to climb/dive, for instance, aeroplanes that want to use the banking feature.

VEHICLE_FLAG_NO_DEFLECTION_UP.tooltip: This flag prevents linear deflection parallel to world z-axis. This is useful for preventing ground vehicles with large linear deflection, like bumper cars, from climbing their linear deflection into the sky.

VEHICLE_HOVER_EFFICIENCY.tooltip: A slider between minimum (0.0 = bouncy) and maximum (1.0 = fast as possible) damped motion of the hover behavior.

VEHICLE_HOVER_HEIGHT.tooltip: The height (above the terrain or water, or global) at which the vehicle will try to hover.

VEHICLE_HOVER_TIMESCALE.tooltip: Period of time (in seconds) for the vehicle to achieve its hover height.

VEHICLE_LINEAR_DEFLECTION_EFFICIENCY.tooltip: A slider between minimum (0.0) and maximum (1.0) deflection of linear velocity. That is, its a simple scalar for modulating the strength of linear deflection.

VEHICLE_LINEAR_DEFLECTION_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The timescale for exponential success of linear deflection deflection. It is another way to specify how much time it takes for the vehicles linear velocity to be redirected to its preferred axis of motion.

VEHICLE_LINEAR_FRICTION_TIMESCALE.tooltip:
A vector of timescales for exponential decay of the vehicles linear velocity along its preferred axes of motion (at, left, up).
			Range = [0.07, inf) seconds for each element of the vector.

VEHICLE_LINEAR_MOTOR_DECAY_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The timescale for exponential decay of the linear motors magnitude.

VEHICLE_LINEAR_MOTOR_DIRECTION.tooltip:
The direction and magnitude (in preferred frame) of the vehicles linear motor. The vehicle will accelerate (or decelerate if necessary) to match its velocity to its motor.
			Range of magnitude = [0, 30] meters/second.

VEHICLE_LINEAR_MOTOR_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The timescale for exponential approach to full linear motor velocity.

VEHICLE_REFERENCE_FRAME.tooltip: A rotation of the vehicles preferred axes of motion and orientation (at, left, up) with respect to the vehicles local frame (x, y, z).

VEHICLE_TYPE_AIRPLANE.tooltip: Uses linear deflection for lift, no hover, and banking to turn.\nSee http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/VEHICLE_TYPE_AIRPLANE

VEHICLE_TYPE_BALLOON.tooltip: Hover, and friction, but no deflection.\nSee http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/VEHICLE_TYPE_BALLOON

VEHICLE_TYPE_BOAT.tooltip: Hovers over water with lots of friction and some anglar deflection.\nSee http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/VEHICLE_TYPE_BOAT

VEHICLE_TYPE_CAR.tooltip: Another vehicle that bounces along the ground but needs the motors to be driven from external controls or timer events.\nSee http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/VEHICLE_TYPE_CAR

VEHICLE_TYPE_SLED.tooltip: Simple vehicle that bumps along the ground, and likes to move along its local x-axis.\nSee http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/VEHICLE_TYPE_SLED

VEHICLE_VERTICAL_ATTRACTION_EFFICIENCY.tooltip: A slider between minimum (0.0 = wobbly) and maximum (1.0 = firm as possible) stability of the vehicle to keep itself upright.

VEHICLE_VERTICAL_ATTRACTION_TIMESCALE.tooltip: The period of wobble, or timescale for exponential approach, of the vehicle to rotate such that its preferred "up" axis is oriented along the worlds "up" axis.

WATER_FRESNEL.tooltip: Fresnel scattering applied to the surface of the water.

WATER_NORMAL_SCALE.tooltip: Scaling applied to the water normal map.

WATER_NORMAL_TEXTURE.tooltip: Normal map used for environmental waves.

WATER_REFRACTION.tooltip: Refraction factors when looking through the surface of the water.

WATER_TEXTURE_DEFAULTS.tooltip: Is the environment using the default wave map.

WATER_WAVE_DIRECTION.tooltip: Vectors for the directions of the waves.

XP_ERROR_EXPERIENCES_DISABLED.tooltip: The region currently has experiences disabled.

XP_ERROR_EXPERIENCE_DISABLED.tooltip: The experience owner has temporarily disabled the experience.

XP_ERROR_EXPERIENCE_SUSPENDED.tooltip: The experience has been suspended by Linden Customer Support.

XP_ERROR_INVALID_EXPERIENCE.tooltip: The script is associated with an experience that no longer exists.

XP_ERROR_INVALID_PARAMETERS.tooltip: One of the string arguments was too big to fit in the key-value store.

XP_ERROR_KEY_NOT_FOUND.tooltip: The requested key does not exist.

XP_ERROR_MATURITY_EXCEEDED.tooltip: The content rating of the experience exceeds that of the region.

XP_ERROR_NOT_FOUND.tooltip: The sim was unable to verify the validity of the experience. Retrying after a short wait is advised.

XP_ERROR_NOT_PERMITTED.tooltip: This experience is not allowed to run by the requested agent.

XP_ERROR_NOT_PERMITTED_LAND.tooltip: This experience is not allowed to run on the current region.

XP_ERROR_NO_EXPERIENCE.tooltip: This script is not associated with an experience.

XP_ERROR_QUOTA_EXCEEDED.tooltip: An attempted write data to the key-value store failed due to the data quota being met.

XP_ERROR_REQUEST_PERM_TIMEOUT.tooltip: Request timed out; permissions not modified.

XP_ERROR_RETRY_UPDATE.tooltip: A checked update failed due to an out of date request.

XP_ERROR_STORAGE_EXCEPTION.tooltip: Unable to communicate with the key-value store.

XP_ERROR_STORE_DISABLED.tooltip: The key-value store is currently disabled on this region.

XP_ERROR_THROTTLED.tooltip: The call failed due to too many recent calls.
